The best approach for new IT-based start-ups to aim both Islam and Chinese markets would be to conduct thorough market research and tailor their products and services to meet the specific needs and preferences of each market. Two key things to consider are cultural and linguistic differences, as well as local regulations and compliance requirements. It would also be beneficial to establish partnerships or collaborations with local businesses and organizations in each market to gain a better understanding of the market and to increase brand awareness and credibility. Additionally, having a strong online presence and utilizing digital marketing strategies can be an effective way to reach these markets.


